Civil judgments for debt declined in September, in keeping with the general trend that has been in place for the past four years.The number of civil judgments for debt fell 7.2% compared with a year earlier, and the value of those judgments was 3.8% smaller than a year ago.For the quarter, the total number of civil judgements recorded for debt was 8% lower than in the third quarter of 2015, while the total value fell 10.9% from a year earlier.Civil summonses for debt increased, however, rising 2.1% in September from September 2015, and increasing 1% in the third quarter compared with a year earlier, Statistics SA data showed on Thursday.The overall trend for civil judgments for debt has been a steady decline over the past four year, while summonses have levelled off over the past year, after three years of declining.